FBIS4-24311 "drafr125_d_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola FAA Reportedly Gaining Ground in Kuito FAA Reportedly Gaining Ground in Kuito MB2806155394 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 1200 GMT 28 Jun 94 MB2806155394 Luanda Radio Nacional Network Portuguese BFN [Excerpt] The winds are changing course in the city of Kuito, Bie Province. The Angolan Armed Forces [FAA] are reversing the situation in the city. They have reoccupied (Tetecole) area, 4 km from Kunje. Fierce clashes have been reported in Kuito and Kunje over the past 24 hours. Abel Abraao reports: As is always the case, the FAA forces in Kuito and Kunje continue to defend civilians, inflicting heavy defeats on Jonas Savimbi's illegal army. This was revealed by the commander of the FAA detachment in Kunje Commune. [passage omitted]
